National Bank of Kuwait (NBK)  said it has
no exposure to derivatives and that it applies international
standards in hedging against  interest rates  and foreign exchange
fluctuations, according to a statement to the Kuwait bourse
today.  The lender said it was not in violation of the countryâ€™s
central bank rules. The comment was in reaction to a local
